### Description

Original proposition was posted as https://github.com/angular/angular/issues/44603 and is well described there.

### Proposed solution

New class in the manner of

```
import {
  AbstractControl,
  AbstractControlOptions,
  AsyncValidatorFn,
  FormArray,
  ValidatorFn, ɵFormArrayRawValue
} from '@angular/forms';

export class FormTuple<TValue, TControl extends AbstractControl = any> extends FormArray<TControl> {
  constructor(
    private readonly controlFactory: (value: TValue) => TControl,
    validatorOrOpts?: ValidatorFn | ValidatorFn[] | AbstractControlOptions | null,
    asyncValidator?: AsyncValidatorFn | AsyncValidatorFn[] | null
  ) {
    super([], validatorOrOpts, asyncValidator);
  }

  override setValue(value: ɵFormArrayRawValue<TControl>, options?: { onlySelf?: boolean; emitEvent?: boolean }) {
    this.syncControls(value, options);
    super.setValue(value, options);
  }

  private syncControls(value: ɵFormArrayRawValue<TControl>, options?: { onlySelf?: boolean; emitEvent?: boolean }) {
    while (this.controls.length > 0) {
      this.removeAt(0, options);
    }
    for (const elementValue of value) {
      this.push(this.controlFactory(elementValue));
    }
  }
}
```

usage:

```
new FormGroup({
  name: new FormControl(),
  children: new FormTuple(
    (value) => new FormGroup({
      name: new FormControl(),
    })
  )
});
```

### Alternatives considered

Manually rebuilding the formGroup with and formArray before doing 

```
const receivedValue = {
  name: "Adam",
  children: [{name: "John"},{name: "Marry"}]
};
this.formGroup = // ... some big manual method to rebuild the form group based on the receivedValue 
this.formGroup.setValue(receivedValue);
```

which may be impossible if an framework to manage forms is used and somewhat defeats the point of reactive forms in my opinion

